args: What was I thinking?! The entire point of\nthe game was for Elly to enjoy herself!
It accomplishes nothing if I am\nhogging all the fun.
Perhaps volleyball was a bad idea;\nit got my competitive juices flowing.
But there might yet be a way for me\nto get Elly into the vacation spirit!
That's right. It's about that time of day,\nwouldn't you agree?
It's something I make a point to enjoy\nwhenever I visit our private beach.
Here, permit me to fill your cup.
Ah, but not conventional black tea!\nThis has been ice brewed.

It's an especially refined and extravagant
way of making tea in which the leaves
are steeped by water from melting ice
in order to extract a fuller flavor.
Well, that DOES sound extravagant!\nI am eager to try it. *sip*
My, it's much sweeter than normal tea!
That is because of the ice brewing.
By steeping it slowly and at extremely low\ntemperatures, one can prevent the usual\nbitterness from emerging.
And all the extra time and trouble results\nin a superior flavor. Yes, I quite like it.
Thank you for introducing this to me.\nI shall have to try making some myself.
I am so pleased that you enjoyed it.\n...But then again, it WAS my idea,\nso that comes as little surprise.
(I did it! Elly REALLY liked it!)
(This experience will surely ease her\ninto a state of relaxation that... Huh?!)
*sniff* What IS that enchanting smell?\nAnd is that smoke I see over there?
*sniff* It has a savory aroma.\nAlmost like...barbecue?
Wait, there actually IS a barbecue?
Oh, this is horrible! The delicate flavor of\nmy tea can't possibly compete with this!
Er, shall we move upwind, Elisanne?
I fear the smoke here is beginning to\ninterfere with the aroma of the tea.
This should do! Now I'll just lay out\nthe tea again and...
Ah! The wind is picking up!
Whoa, that caught me by surprise!\nYou okay there, Ranzal?
What matters is that the GRUB is all right.\nTime to throw the next batch on the grill!
And now the smoke is in our faces again.\nThat's it—I am going to complain!
I don't think that is necessary.
But it is! You can't possibly enjoy the\naroma of the tea under such conditions!
Honestly, it is the most minor of—
We need you to stop your barbecue.\nThe smoke is unacceptable.
Ya can't have a barbecue without smoke,\nyeah? Ain't much I can do about that.
Yes, that's why I'm asking you to stop.

Moreover, scarcely any time has passed
since lunch! Is your goal to see everyone
become gluttonous hogs who must roll
about the beach in order to perambulate?!
Bwaaa ha ha! Hell, we're an active bunch;\nwe'll just work off what we eat.
So how come ya want us to stop NOW?
I didn't hear any complaints from\nyou at lunch.
There's a time and a place for barbecue,\nbut it is not NOW.
All of your smoke has completely ruined\nthe aroma of my ice-brewed tea!
Ya mean the stuff ya got there? *sniff*\nHey, that smells pretty good!
Well then, perhaps I should take this\nopportunity to introduce you to my\nspecial summer tea recipe.
Once you appreciate the delicate charms\nof ice-brewed tea, you will understand the\ndamage caused by your filthy smoke!
Let us begin by outlining the steps\nrequired to properly prepare it...
...And that is how you ice brew tea.\nNow do you have a better appreciation\nfor the intricacies involved?
Damn, that was a long explanation.\nMy throat's dry as a bone!
I didn't realize that there was so much\ninvolved in brewing tea.
Knowledge is at the root of refinement.\nI'm glad you had this chance to learn.
You are a fine teacher, Julietta, and most\nknowledgeable in the subject matter.
Oh, it's not an especially difficult topic.
But if you are interested, there is a great\ndeal more I could teach you about tea,\nsuch as how the leav—
All right, we get it! Just lemme guzzle\ndown the damn tea before my withered\nhusk dries up and blows away!
Tea is not a beverage to be ＂guzzled,＂ sir!\nFirst, you must breathe in the aroma and—
Was that your stomach growling, Ranzal?\nThere truly is no end to your appetite.
Ain't me—my gut is full to burstin'\nwith sweet barbecue.
It wasn't me, either. Maybe someone...\nUh, Julietta? Why are you blushing?
C-certainly not because it was ME!\nI am a woman of refinement.
If yer hungry, just say so.
Did you not have much to eat at lunch?
(He's right—I was so preoccupied with\nElly that I completely forgot to eat!)
Maybe you should have a little\nbarbecue with your tea.
Damn straight! Ain't nothin' better than\nfine chow washed down with tea.
Were you not listening when I explained\nhow barbecue smoke ruins the aroma?
Here you go! Fresh off the grill.
(It wasn't supposed to happen like this...\nBut next time, I will—Yeowch! That's hot!)
